Okay, so the next question is, what
kind of backend stack do we want to use?

00:00:03.580 --> 00:00:06.200
Now, I really want to get something
that's going to be quick to set up,

00:00:06.200 --> 00:00:09.030
because we should get Shopping
List Plus Plus in users' hands as

00:00:09.030 --> 00:00:10.630
fast as possible.

00:00:10.630 --> 00:00:12.240
I'm pretty solid with Android, but

00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:14.210
it's been a really long time
since I set up a server.

00:00:14.210 --> 00:00:16.180
&gt;&gt; Well,
maybe you don't need to set up a server.

00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:21.191
Have you ever heard of [SOUND] Firebase?

00:00:21.191 --> 00:00:24.186
&gt;&gt; Hm, well, I'm intrigued,
I have heard of Firebase,

00:00:24.186 --> 00:00:26.477
it's like a fancy database, right?

